rcial bank headquartered in texas and is on the list of largest banks in the united states the companys largest offices are in detroit livonia auburn hills michigan and dallas contents  history  corporate responsibility  see also  references  external links historyedit the company was founded in detroit by elon farnsworth in  as the detroit savings fund institute its name changed to the detroit savings bank in  and to the detroit bank in  being one of the few area banks to survive the great depression in  the company merged with birmingham national bank ferndale national bank and detroit wabeek bank and trust company to form the detroit bank  trust company in  it formed a holding company detroitbank corporation the current name was adopted in  in  comerica entered the florida market in  it acquired its hometown rival bank of the commonwealth of michigan it entered the texas market in  when it acquired grand bancshares it added the california market in  when it purchased plaza commerce bancorp and inbancshares in  comerica received approval to construct a new headquarters building one detroit center in  comerica merged with a similarlysized detroitbased bank manufacturers national corporation in  comerica sold its illinois operation to lasalle bank parent abn amro for  million in  comerica signed a year  million agreement for the naming rights to comerica park in downtown detroit home to the detroit tigers of major league baseball in  comerica sold its credit card division to mbna and formed an alliance with the company in  comerica acquired imperial bank of california which also had branches in arizona on march   the company announced its decision to relocate its corporate headquarters to dallas in order to move closer to its customer base in the sun belt in august the company announced that it selected  main street in downtown dallas the company executives began moving into  main street in november  and the building was renamed comerica tower in january  the company was selected by the united states department of the treasury as the issuing bank for its direct express debitcard program the federal government uses the express debit product to issue electronic payments such as social security benefits to people who do not have bank accounts unbanked in july  comerica completed the acquisition of houstonbased sterling bank texas for  billion which greatly expanded operations in texas corporate responsibilityedit in  comerica provided more than  million to notforprofit organizations in its markets its employees raised more than  million for the united way and black united fund and donated their personal time with more than  hours spent helping to make a positive difference in the communities it serves comerica has established a plan for reducing carbon emissions and has reported its progress in meeting its sustainability goals see alsoedit business and economics portal companies portal dallasfort worth portal detroit portal comerica bank building san diego california comerica bank challenger tennis tournament comerica bank new years parade dallas texas list of largest banks in the united states list of companies in dallas list of michigan companies referencesedit  a b c d e f g h comerica incorporated  form k annual report us securities and exchange commission   comerica celebrates  years of banking press release prnewswire october     a b c d comerica  years in detroit crain communications march     a b c d e f g h i comerica company history  bates james september   foray has begun michigan firm to buy bank in state los angeles times   building plan in detroit starts debate the new york times august     quint michael october   banks plan a merger in detroit the new york times   comerica rival will merge in stock swap associated press los angeles times october     comerica to sell illinois banking unit to abn amro the new york times march     shea bill february   comerica signs sponsorship deal for new red wings arena crain commu